                <h1>Understanding the Meaning of the Yellow Wallpaper</h1>
                <p>The "Yellow Wallpaper" symbolizes the oppression of women in the 19th century and the struggle for self-identity. The wallpaper itself represents the constraints placed on women, mirroring the protagonist's descent into madness as she seeks freedom. Ultimately, it highlights themes of mental health, confinement, and personal liberation.</p>
